caption: Great food & drinks
Only 1 server was wearing a mask. Food is okay
Great healthy options, esp for anyone gluten-free. Just wish their delivery was faster.
It’s amazing to find such a tasty, completely gluten free, restaurant. Pizza was awesome! Great atmosphere, even in the pandemic
nice array of food and desserts. The portions are quite generous and filling. Also, highly recommend the Bordeaux they have.
Love the place and their happy hour deal))). Great service,  waitress and bartender were super nice and friendly. Delicious food.
Great oyster happy hour deal

As a restaurant, it's solid, as a gluten free restaurant it is fantastic. Local mozzarella pizza was good pie even compared to a wheat flour pie. Roasted beet salad was satisfying. The chicken parm was very "new york." Lots of cheese, sauce, and a huge bed of spaghetti. The happy hour dollar oysters didn't hurt either.
It is my 2nd time there ,its pretty good .
Great Service, Atmosphere,Food, Music🎶,Waiter, Bar,🍸 Happy Hour!!! Will Return To This Great 👍 Place...
amazing. and gluten free! came here with my roommate with celiacs and it’s very well labeled. food was phenomenal. highly recommend.
A little more pricey than just an everyday lunch, but certainly delicious! My partner even loved it and they aren't gluten-free. So nice to have a place that we can both enjoy for a special day out!

The best gluten-free pizza in Brooklyn! Get the penne alla vodka pizza. This restaurant is such an amazing stand-by for dinner with the gluten-sensitive. Cocktails and pasta are okay. Sitting on the patio was a lovely ambience, even in pandemic times.

I visited here with my friends and I honestly the service and the food was amazing. Our server, Eduardo, was really respectful, kind and humorous it was an overall great experience especially because of him.
I loved the food loved, the service.  I will definitely come back very often!!! Such an amazing place made me feel warm and welcome at this very crazy time.
Amazing Italian food 100% gluten free!

Had delivery through Uber eats. Driver called and asked us to come down to the street to collect. Once finalised, an order for 2 Pastas and 1 pizza with vegan cheese came to $87!!! The worst food with zero flavor.
Amazing food, good service and there is a beer garden that allows to bring beer to restaurant. The food is all kinds of natural.
Absolutely no gluten anywhere in the restaurant, and it was all super delicious. They also have gf and vegan options.

Food is tasty and the atmosphere very pleasant. Unfortunately server was very rude to the point of slamming a plate on the table, I was eating mussels and my wife was done with her salad, she pick the bowl with the shells and ask me if I was ok to use my wife’s dirty bowl for the  rest of the shells. But  I wasn’t ready to ruin our first restaurant meal in almost 5 months.
Extremely rude waiters and manager. Very slow service.

OMG. Outstanding food in park Slope! From the wine, beer, cocktails and sparkling water appetizers and salads are amazing. The pasta dish I had Was butternut squash ravio in a butter sage sauce ,  strawberry and goat cheese topped bruschetta and a mushroom and truffle Pizza topped with shredded parmesan cheese and arugula  and wow it was great!  Very fresh ingredients and friendly staff . We Definitely will be back !   And you should definitely check them out .
Awesome food for everyone

O.v.e.r.p.r.i.c.e.d. Keep walking, they collect $65.00 without letting you pass Go.  Their hummus includes literally 3 baby carrots, 3 small celery slices, and 8 chips for $14. A joke. Also, you get 6 small shishito peppers and aoli for $8 under their Happy Hour menu. This is the kind of place that should go out of business because of the pandemic.
Very attentive and friendly staff. Great experience.

We just ordered delivery from here and it was amazing! The peanut butter mouse brownie was fantastic. Highly recommend the Butternut Squash Ravioli & the Fresh Burratta. Again I will mention the brownie!
Great management and excellent atmosphere! Our waitress Beatrix gave us outstanding service! I strongly recommend this restaurant Thank you!
Great food. Nice cozy place!

Overpriced mediocre food and mediocre service.  I came to Wild Park Slope with a few friends for brunch and the best part about it was that we were able to make a reservation. After our food arrived I realized why!  Each plate (which has to come with coffee) cost about $20. My frittata was burnt on the bottom and very bland. The included toast had no butter but at least the home fries were tasty and well cooked if a bit mushy.  The city has so many great spots for brunch. Find one of those and skip Wild Park Slope.
Overpriced.  Bad service.  Pizza crust taste like chemicals.  I order a pepperoni pizza once.  6 slices, 4 pepperonis.

Nice and comfortable place,  the staff is very professional and friendly, the food is delicious. Special thanks to the kitchen staff they really know how to make us happy with the food. 🔪🥄🧂🏆👨‍🍳👨‍🍳 definitely coming back
Great oyster happy hour with excellent blues and clams. Good location, excellent menu, great owner and staff. Go there.
This place has AMAZING drinks and great food options! Big Al took care of us and was super attentive throughout our whole time there! Love it!  Try the pineapple infused Tito’s! 😍 🍍
Good happy hr, and owner is very friendly as well as staff
Salad with grilled chicken was delicious. We had a vegetable pizza, it was awful. The crust was chewy and undercooked.

A solid meh. The entire menu is gluten-free, which is what gives them 3 stars instead of 2. I had an omelette with mushrooms, spinach, and goat cheese. The mushrooms looked and tasted like they came out of a can. I can’t imagine that they did, but they sure seemed like it. The spinach was cooked well, but lacked any seasoning. The goat cheese saved this omelette. GF toast needed butter or jam or anything, but it was a pretty decent GF bread product. Potatoes were good. Coffee wasn’t good. Service was fine. I’ll give this place another try, but today it totally fell flat.

First time here. Stopped in for dinner and was happy to find a great Happy Hour. $5 drinks & $1 oysters & clams. Friendly staff and cool vibe.  I had some half shells and chicken penne w/pesto.  Very good and nice flavor, gluten free too. Oysters and clams were fresh. I'll be back to try other dishes. Thanks -

I just visited last week for the first time and had a phenomenal experience. The food was light, fresh, and super tasty. The service was attentive but not overbearing. And they have happy hour 7 days a week with $5 drinks and delicious seafood. Plus I discovered as I was leaving that everything is also 100% gluten-free which is awesome but I would've never known the difference in taste. I will definitely be back again soon!
really amazing gluten free food! they also were super accommodating to all food allergies like dairy.  highly recommend! not pictured here is the calamari which was super tender!

The food was absolutely delicious! The staff was amazing and super friendly. They helped me pick one of the most fantastic dishes my pallet has ever experienced. 5 stars all around! Definitely recommend to everyone! Thank you so much, Marina!
Everything was gluten free, even delicious desserts
So wish it was better! Hate to give GF a bad review...
The food is mediocre and the portions are small. The price they are charging is not justified.

My dish, the butternut squash ravioli, was DELICIOUS! My partners seafood dish wasn't great. I didn't really like the red sauce on it myself but she seemed to like it. The music was too loud for a Tuesday night but that's maybe more a matter of opinion than anything else.
Service was great.
I was only here for "happy hour" to treat my sister-in-law to drinks, and I must say it was fantastic:Five dollar Titos, and dollar oysters and clams; who can beat it? Great bartender and ambiance.
Took my mom there. The whole place is gluten free.  She loved it.

Friendly chill atmosphere
Pizza delivered cold and wasn’t anything to write home about! Won’t order takeout from them again.
Really enjoyed the atmosphere, food and felt safe eating here as a celiac.
Loved the gluten-free choices of gourmet food

I ordered pizza it was the worst pizza in the world. When I called to complain some Russian lady spoke to said she was the owner. I never heard of Russians making good pizzas. Stay away if don't want to waste your time and money and your appitite. And the owner was very rude.

DO NOT EAT HERE! SO MANY OTHER OPTIONS IN THE NEIGHBORHOOD!  Slow service. Server did not tell us there were specials, we spotted them after we already ordered on a board indoors. We were sat outside. Our server never came to ask how the food was, nor to refill our drinks or water.  We ordered 2 pizzas and salad w avo etc. Pizzas were ok for gluten free. Cheese was nothing special. The prosciutto pizza had tabasco thrown all over it- very lazy. The basil on the pizza was diced so small- it was sad and tasteless. The salads had HAIR IN THEM. Several strands of short black hair. Pieces of lettuce were wilted, cherry tomatoes were obviously pre- cut- not cut to order. The chicken was dry and tasteless. The salad had hardly any dressing on it. And - the corn that was meant to be in the salad, which was on menu was dnot in the salad. When we asked why our salad  came with no corn, we were told “oh, its not available, we ran out and dont offer the corn anymore but haven’t changed the menu”.  The lemonade was made from concentrate. As a former chef and server, I had to give bad reviews-  but truly- this place needs to revamp or close up shop.

Seriously, just don't go here. Cannot believe it stays open. As many reviews have noted the service is shockingly slow and terrible. To the point of actually just being confusing - have never experienced service like this in NYC. When we complained (literally took one full hour to tell us they were out of what we ordered) and asked for a drink or appetizer comped, they flat out said they don't do that, and told us we could just not leave a tip...  so weird. Don't be fooled by the hip looking bar/decor like we were! You've been warned.
Very very Good .

Great Happy Hour! I've been to this place many times now. I really enjoyed my time there. Their happy hour is pretty decent, Mon-Sun. Mimosas, Mloody Marys, all all that. I've had the oysters, also very nice. Everything has been submitted fine, but the service. Not that the service was rude, it is just very "new" very inexperienced, and slow. I will update this review as time goes on and they get better. I really wish them well. Give them a visit.

Not wild about this place at all. Flatbread fell flat with undercooked and underseasoned veggies. The place didn't seem clean to me and the chairs and tables desperately need to be replaced.  Why was the service so slow when the restaurant was nearly empty? There are much better establishments in the neighborhood that offer good tasting food with much more attentive service.
Okay drinks but service was quite slow.

Their pizza is not the best in town,  however they have a decent variety,  some fairly artisanal. What sets them apart is that all their pizzas are gluten free and all are available with goat cheese or vegan cheese substituting the usual mozzarella if you want. So if you're on a gluten-free or dairy-free diet and miss eating pizza,  this place is awesome.  Also, whatever non-pizza dishes I've tried at Wild were very good but overpriced.

I was really excited for this place, as it is a 100% gluten free restaurant. But I didn't think the food was very good, or at least what I ordered. The bruschetta was a piece of sad looking toast and the butternut squash ravioli had a super buttery sauce. I would be willing to go again and try another dish, since 100% GF kitchens are rare!

Delivery came and called from up the street claiming he couldn’t deliver to our door (the exact point of getting delivery). When we told him that wasn’t acceptable he marked it as “delivered” but alas, he didn’t deliver anything. The restaurant said they had no control over their drivers. Cool cool cool.
Good gluten free options

The cafe was cute, service was great, food was pretty good. I liked that everything was gluten free and still delicious!  The shrimp scampi was AMAZING and I can't recommend it enough. The rest of the food was pretty good as well. Definitely a spot to check out.
This little spot on 5th Ave has a nice ambiance. The design is simple and pleasant. The issues are that they are understaffed and the food is not good

First time I went with my wife, after a meal which was ok, they brought me a dessert which was old and stale, obviously from the display tray.  Yesterday was 10x worse. Our server fd up our order, and brought us 3 pizzas instead of two (remember, me and my wife). Then confronted us aggressively about how we were at fault. We then ask for the manager/owner. She was equally useless and rude and basically said the whole ordeal was our fault. Said she was going to see what she could do, but didn't do anything. Just sat in the back and was on her phone the whole time. At least they didn't charge us for the server's mistake. Nice to have a gluten free place close to our apartment since my wife has celiac, but never ever coming back to this place.  It was prophetic when someone passed in front of the place and shouted "worst service ever!", then 20 mins later another lady walked by and said to her friend "happy hour here is not so happy".  Most restaurants in NYC fail even if run well, this one has its days counted.

I have Celiac Disease so I was happy to find Wild and had eaten there once before.  My husband and I had ordered a large pizza which the server said is actually two, at first we said fine then he had to go ask about a beer before he could finish our order, then he came back and I ask to change the food order. I said so since a large is 2 pizzas I think we are just going to get one and order a different pizza instead. We both felt we were clear, and he says okay, doesn't check to see if we are ordering three. (also we are just two people) Our food comes out and there are three pizzas. We sent one back, because we didn't order three.  The server comes back and confronts us, said he asked if two was okay and we said fine. He was rude and unapologetic. I have never had that happen before. I said yes then you came back and we asked to change our order. He proceeded to insist he was right,  making us very uncomfortable. I asked to speak to a manager, mainly because I have never been confronted by a server for a misunderstanding.  She said the server is responsible for mistakes and he had every right to confront us. At least now I know why he behaved so badly. What a terrible idea, so if a mistake happens you want servers to start fights with costumers? It ruined the meal at that point.  Won't come back.
Polite waitress, underwhelming pizza (gluten free crust), desserts are gluten free so they tasted meh too. OK Guacamole.
Half empty and still mad slow
I got pizza it was ok I want to go back and try the pasta
Everything was delicious!
Small portions for $$$

Nice decor and menu but was a little put off by the gluten free buffalo chicken pizza. The crust was too hard . Otherwise the rest was great... good brunch spot for a couple or just friends wanting a chat.
Great drinks and amazing food
Food was delicious! Wonderful service.
Everything was excellent, literally everything, Coeliac heaven. The atmosphere and staff were lovely too.
Amazing!! Everything is gluten free!!!
Interesting concept. I thought it was good and I’m glad I tried it, but I’m not sure it makes my list of places I must try again.

This place is so adorable!!! I've been searching everywhere for a 100 percent gulten free restaurant for my sister who has a severe allergy to gulten and found this place the food was DELICIOUS and when I say DELICIOUS my sister ordered 2 entrees for herself. I ordered shrimp scampi highly recommend pasta tasted like pasta I make at home only better you cant even tell the difference we also ordered the nachos as soon as it hit out table we devoured it in a matter of seconds!! I love to eat especially when the food is outrageously DELICIOUS but it makes it even more enjoyable that I could bring my sister along and not have to fear her ending up sick. We will be returning worth the toll from staten island!!!!
Great vegan options!!!
$1 oysters before 7pm. Really good ones. Nummy num nums!

Love, love, love. Definitely intend on going back.  I'm surprised that it was empty tonight but also very happy.  The waitress was friendly and very knowledgeable of the menu.  The loaded chicken nachos were great.  My friend had the pizza with vegan cheese which was surprisingly tasty. I had the zoodles which was also very good.  Topped it off with a vegan brownie! I think if you try this place you will not be disappointed.  Oh, the food is gluten free!

This place is awful. We waited over 90 minutes for ice cold and I mean ICE cold food. Paid $15 for alleged asparagus parmigiana which consisted of 4 pieces of asparagus and all the sauce was swimming in the bag. Every package of food we ordered was smashed. Never ordering from here again. 👎🏼
Gf and amazing ❤❤
That is not pizza. Stop calling that pizza. Salad on a bad cracker is not pizza.
love it
Nice looking place, nice staff. My beer & salad were excellent.
Nice cocktails and selection of wine, great service and gluten free meals
Everything is gluten free AND the food is really good
Tasty pizza

Loved this restaurant - dark, cozy, and romantic. Delicious food and 100% gluten-free! I didn't think I could ever find gf food that tastes like the real deal but this is it. Definitely recommend checking this place out and try their current seasonal special, the Pumpkin Martini. Soooo good!!
Good gluten-free menu. Food good. Service caused the eating to drop from 5-stars
Excellent food, varied menu, outside seating, decent wait staff, and absolutely terrific coffee.
Totally Overpriced

Server was nice but wait was excessive for our food considering they were not very busy. The food was extremely bland. Almost like they didn't salt anything. Had the chicken parmigiano and may as well have been cardboard parmigiano.
Good gluten free ravioli.  Chicken parm was tasty too.  Really great ambiance with friendly staff.
Everything was great.  100% Gluten free. We will be going back.
Awesome place for diner

Food was very good, and Alex (server) was super friendly. Ordered the wild mushroom truffle penne, which was great. Also had peanut butter brownie for dessert (and I don't even like peanut butter) but this thing was amazing!

Not sure why this place doesn’t have five stars... it’s been one of my go to restaurants for years. Awesome menus, fabulous gluten free dinner (brunch is even better). Among my favorites are the tofu breakfast scramble, mushroom bruschetta, and mozz sticks. Amazing dessert too. The waiters and waitresses are always strikingly friendly. I’ve never left this place unsatisfied !
Incredibly slow service, and found a hair in both of our meals.
Excellent
Nice to be able to relax in a fully gluten-free setting. Great food too!

Came all the way from South Carolina to try the zucchini noodle dish.  When we arrived we were told to find a seat(it was empty inside).  When the server finally came over, she told us that they did not have pizza.  Well that really limits the menu since about half of the menu is pizza.  So, we left since the others in our party were going to order pizza.  How can you have a pizza place with no PIZZA?  Maybe try one of the other locations, but I would not waste your time traveling to this one.
Wow that was SO GOOD. Ohmygosh everyone needs to get the mozz sticks. Also the marina is AMAZING. I'm sure the pizzas are delicious!!! Also the drinks are 10/10 especially during happy hour.
I really enjoyed the happy hour specials. The gluten free items tasted really great, and the service and food tasted great!

I went here because someone in our party is gluten free, we got there and 4 out of 5 of our water glasses were dirty, it took forever to get clean ones, forever to place our drink order and forever to get our food, and it wasn't busy. One of the people in my party wouldn't eat her pizza because it had a terrible taste to it, the rest of us mostly ate, but we were not overly impressed with the food. I wouldn't go here again
Terrible service. Mediocre food. Just no. So many better places in the Slope.
Food was ok but 5 stars for service!
Delicious gluten free food — awesome pizza (option with vegan cheese!!)

Every time I place a order they get it wrong. I really use to like this place. The day I first came in there was a more mature lady with glasses very sharp and polite. Lately I’ve experience a younger staff that seems to not hear well at all or they don’t care about the task at hand. I’m a lvegan I hold true to my values and no one who is a vegan what to order a vegan pizza and have a  mozzarella (dairy) pizza waiting. I work all day and really want that slice I’ll try to come if she is in but they really have been dropping the ball lately, the male staff I say because I haven’t experienced any mismanagement of any of my orders when it’s taken by any female. Sad thing is I drove from NJ to get the pie.
The gluten free French toast was amazing! We went back a few days later in the evening to try the pizza - glad we did. What a gem.
Great pasta spot

I was there for the first time and absolutely loved the food. However, a family allowed their children to run and play throughout the restaurant, which made my and other patrons' experience unpleasant.

eh pasta was alright, the pizza was good though! Bread was just regular toast?????

Wild is a fantastic 100% gluten free establishment in park slope with many vegan options as well. We always leave full and satisfied with great service! Last time we were treated to complimentary dessert! This is a peanut butter brownie and it was DELICIOUS

The food was so bad. I'm convinced the chicken was microwaved Tysons and everything was soaked in salt. It took 1.5+ hours to get food. We received free wine for our troubles but even that tasted awful. It was my worst restaurant experience ever.
A Fantastic Gluten Free Restaurant!  Was a treat to have Mozzarella Sticks again!
Nice enough. Above average. Good concepts, but was not wowed

The shakshuka was really good. The wild salad was good, and so was the moscow mule, but the pizza is what I'd expect from a bowling alley. It was undercooked, and they put prosciutto in clumps on the pizza after it was cooked, making it gray and not good. The pizza also tasted heavily of capers.  Service is slow because they have one busboy and one server for brunch. I didn't finish a whole drink before they brought the food like the other reviewer, but it was a little close.  I'm assuming the owner is skimping on ingredients and the kitchen is trying their best with the minimal ingredients they have. Even just including more hearty bread with the shakshuka is a good start.
Friendly staff but the coffee was sub par
Consistently great food, and surprisingly quality salads! Also friendly staff:)
Great place! Healthy food at a good price point. Staff is super friendly and accommodating.

Came here for a 3rd time for my wife's bday with friends and the food was delicious and the staff was exceptionally attentive and pleasant. I love this place more and more. I can't wait to go back! Delicious soups, honey avocado toasts, pizza, and pesto chicken penne!
Pretty good food, service was a little show
Nice cozy restaurant. Excellent food and great service.

Food is basic and overpriced. Service very slow and cold but if you don’t say goodnight they’ll chase you in the street.

Incredibly slow service. Lackluster food. Waited 45 minutes for our meal and they waited 15 minutes after serving our entrees to serve our third plate. Pizza and pasta were boring and tasteless yet pricey. After our meal the server chased my husband out of the restaurant to say goodnight. Rude.
Waiter was very friendly and attentive!
The waiters were so friendly and helped me pick out a fantasticly tasty meal!

Don't go here. I waited 30 mins for my meal, and it was cold when it came out. When I asked the waiter where it was, he said "I'm not the cooker, I've already checked twice for you." No communication, no apology, I was made to feel bad for asking where my food was. Had I had more time I would have made them take my meal back, so that my eggs, potatoes and English muffin were actually served warm.

well intended service but too few and inattentive. if you ask for salt and pepper it should come right away not let your food get cold.  no cappuccinonor else for a brunch?? also the food was poorly prepped and without any „love“ to detail or looks of the plate.  no jams, no side bread, no butter nothing...  price wise for quality and quantity totally not woth it.

Truffle Sauce for Penne is DISGUSTING. Overpriced food, I wish I had listened to the reviews

Food is not terrible (if you like gluten free pizza crust and bland raw tofu in your salad ), but the business clearly has some issues. The place was way under-staffed, and the poor servers who were there were doing their best to make up for it, but the food just wasn't worth the excessive wait or the excessive prices ($12 for a handful of kale).
Chill place and great food.  Friendly neighborhood place.
Food is overpriced for quality. (Pasta dishes...tried 4 so far)..good atmosphere though.

This place was fantastic! So cute- I loved the decor. The service was great, and the food came out quickly. Our appetizer (bruscetta) and entrees (beet and goat cheese salad, spinach ravioli, and chicken milanese) were delicious and reasonably priced. Great ambiance, great food, great experience!!

It was amazing excellent food and the waitress is so kind I like this place .

Great service. Decent food. Easy and quick sit down spot with simple decor.
The food was fine, but not much different than my own cooking... and I'm not a great cook.  It's a good option if you have anyone gluten-free in your crowd, but I wouldn't go back if not for that.
Too much light, no professional service (dirty cutlery), no dressing on mediocre avocado salad. The place looked clean though, mistakes were corrected and the ravioli were nice.
Tasted good, but made me feel sick.
